thread class methods
--------------------


Thread interrupt
----------------

it is used to interrupt an executing thread

	interruot()
	-----------
	it will only works when the thread is in the wait state() or in sleeping state().
	
	if a thread is not in sleeping or waiting state then calling an interrupt methods(), will perform normal behaviour...it is no use

	isInteruupted()
	---------------
	
	to check whether the thread is interrupted.
	
	interrupted()
	-------------
	
	change the current thread interruption to false, which makes interruption flag of current thread will be change to false.
	which gives that , it is making thread as no interrupted. 

	method checks whether the thread is interrupted or not. if interrupted, the method will clear the state from true to false






















